raw_data.title: Project Manager/Client Services
raw_data.description: Responsible for overall success of work or task order. Identifies and directs cross-functional task teams to accomplish activities. Monitors technical, cost and schedule performance and directs action to resolve real or anticipated problems to ensure timely product delivery.

raw_data.title: Animator* (3D)
raw_data.description: Responsible for concept and design of 3D animations and motion graphics for inclusion in video projects. Coordinates with Creative Director to ensure color, design, fonts and artwork complement and remain consistent throughout project or across campaign platforms. Experience with software such as After Effects or equivalent.
raw_data.education_and_experience_substitution: Associates Degree with 2 additional years' experience

labor_categories.years_experience: Associates Degree with 2 additional years' experience

raw_data.title: Art Director  - Set Designer
raw_data.description: Responsible for overall thematic look and design of set or shoot location; creation or procurement of sets, set pieces and individual scene elements to include backdrops, furnishings, multi-media components, and props.

raw_data.title: Associate Producer
raw_data.description: Assists producer and/or director during shoots, maintains production logbook and crew time sheets. Responsible for ordering crew meals and/or securing craft services.

raw_data.title: Audio Mixer (Post)*
raw_data.description: Responsible for final audio sweetening and mixdown including professional voice over, SOTs, SFXs, and music.

raw_data.title: Audio Technician (Field, ENG)*
raw_data.description: Sound lead while on field shoots, responsible for recording, monitoring and mixing sound during shoots. This includes selection and setup of microphones, mixers, cables, and back-up sound recording device(s).

raw_data.title: Audio Technician (Studio/Live Events)
raw_data.description: Sound engineer for in-studio, broadcast, webcast and/or live event shoots, responsible for recording, monitoring and mixing sound during shoots. This includes selection and setup of microphones, mixers, cables, and back-up sound recording device(s).

raw_data.title: Casting Director
raw_data.description: Responsible for coordinating with Director for talent search per project needs. Coordinates with professional talent agencies or schedules open auditions to secure headshots and schedule audition times. Holds auditions, tapes talent, and submits to Director and Client Team for final selection. Contracts talent upon final selection.

raw_data.title: Continuity Director
raw_data.description: Responsible for insuring continuity between scenes/shots. Must have a keen eye for detail. Shoots and maintains individual scene photo stills during shoots for comparison.

raw_data.title: Creative Director
raw_data.description: Full responsibility for the overall theme, look, composition, lighting and shooting of the production.  Develops concepts and approach for each project. Assists clients in identifying their design needs and provides creative solutions. Responsible for creative cohesiveness of production across all elements.

raw_data.title: Director
raw_data.description: Oversees project in scope and direction. Works with client, producers and writers to ensure that the script fulfills the project's mission. May work with DP and camera operators on camera positions, shot composition and shooting style. Develops shot sheets and determines actor blocking. Involved in talent auditions and final casting. Responsible for direction of professional talent and other on camera personnel. May provide creative direction during post-production.

raw_data.title: Director of Photography (DP)*
raw_data.description: Responsible for shooting principle photography. Responsible for all camera technical operations and principle photography, determines lighting approach, directs lighting crew in implementing approach. Determines camera type and setup (frame rate, shutter speed, white balance, etc.), camera angles and shooting techniques (jib, dolly, etc.). Directs videographers in implementing approach. Works closely with Director in developing shot sheet prior to principle photography.

raw_data.title: DVD Authoring Navigation*
raw_data.description: Responsible for design, layout and navigation for both multi-chapter and straight play DVDs. Knowledge of various authoring software.

raw_data.title: Editor* (Rough Cut) Junior Editor
raw_data.description: Responsible for initiating the first cut edit of projects including rough timeline layout of audio and video elements per client approved script. Cut scratch track audio for voice over narration, create blank slate placeholders for graphics and animation. Experience using various editing hardware and software.

raw_data.title: Editor* (Finish)
raw_data.description: Modifies and completes project, merging media elements into final program to include client revisions, color correction, audio mixdown, graphics, music and voice; renders to a variety of formats. DVD authoring. Ensures mixed format and mixed media have a consistent look.

raw_data.title: Editor* (Senior)
raw_data.description: Member of internal review team. Supervises editors, schedules edit sessions, and signs off on all deliverables before client program delivery. Operates, maintains and updates editing equipment and software systems.

raw_data.title: Engineer Webcast (Studio)
raw_data.description: Responsible for technical coordination of live or live-to-tape studio webcasts. Secures third party services and hardware for live streaming, slide, video or audio pre-loads, and media storage.  Troubleshoots during event.

raw_data.title: Floor Director
raw_data.description: Responsible for disseminating information between the Director, crew, and talent during live and live-to-tape studio shoots. Cues talent and live audience.

raw_data.title: Food Stylist
raw_data.description: Responsible for creating aesthetically pleasing visuals of food for print and video. Must have extensive knowledge of food , its preparation and visual sustainability, as well as knowledge in culinary arts and science.

raw_data.title: Graphic Designer* (LT, Titling)
raw_data.description: Under the direction of the Creative Director, Graphic Designer is responsible for creating lower thirds, titling, and other basic, non-motion graphics for inclusion in video projects. Responsible for reformatting and enhancing client provided artwork including charts, maps, and graphs. Proficient in PhotoShop.

raw_data.title: Graphic Designer* (Print)
raw_data.description: Designs, develops and creates layouts, incorporating illustrations, electronic art, and other graphic elements for visual communication media. Extensive knowledge of programs such as PhotoShop/Illustrator/InDesign or equivalent. Works with still photographers, writers, and photo librarian to secure cleared images for inclusion in design.
raw_data.education_and_experience_substitution: Associates Degree and 2 additional year's experience.

labor_categories.years_experience: Associates Degree and 2 additional year's experience.

raw_data.title: Graphic Designer* (Motion)
raw_data.description: Provides creative animations for use in videos, webcasts, and DVDs.

raw_data.title: Grip (Key)
raw_data.description: Works with the Director of Photography and Lighting Director to help set up and to achieve desired lighting effects and camera positions.

raw_data.title: Grip
raw_data.description: Works under the direction of the key grip or Lighting Director.  Assists both the Lighting Director and Gaffer in lighting, rigging, set construction and other miscellaneous production tasks.  Maintains grip equipment and inventories during breakdown.

raw_data.title: Hair/Makeup Artist* and Wardrobe
raw_data.description: Responsible for preparing hair, face, nails/hands of on camera talent. Experience with makeup application for all types/color of skin, hair (or lack of hair). Familiar with a wide range of makeup, cleansing products and allergen reactions. Assists with wardrobe selection and maintenance while on set.

raw_data.title: Illustrator - Storyboard Artist*
raw_data.description: Responsible for providing visual representation that enhances content or clarifies concepts through either traditional or digital artistic formats. Helps client team visualize concepts through storyboard development.

raw_data.title: Jib Operator*
raw_data.description: Responsible for set up and operation of camera and jib.

raw_data.title: Librarian (Video Archives - Media Management)
raw_data.description: Responsible for set up, updates and maintenance of media archives both in-house and for client media management. Familiarity with media archive software applications; develop and maintain user-friendly search tools. Maintains artist/photographer crediting and licenses for selected media; maintains music and sfx cue sheets.

raw_data.title: Lighting Director
raw_data.description: Designs light plot per production needs, determines and submits equipment needs list, checks in/out lighting equipment for production, sets production lights per light plot. Works with electrics and lighting, manages gaffer/grip production crew.

raw_data.title: Location Scouting
raw_data.description: Responsible for contacting, scouting potential shoot locations, and securing clearances and location release forms. Photographs potential locations and completes checklist of challenges (e.g. noise, traffic, power availability, etc.). Apply for permits and security personnel as needed.

raw_data.title: Music Research*
raw_data.description: Responsible for researching music and sfxs for use in projects. Secures and maintains license agreements; maintains cue sheets for each project.

raw_data.title: Open Captioning* -Transcriptionist
raw_data.description: Responsible for securing and verifying final transcript of production in word.doc format. For languages other than English, responsible for securing font package for edit. Coordinates with finish editor in laying in captions per Section 508 compliance guidelines.

raw_data.title: Photographer (Still)*
raw_data.description: Responsible for digital still photography in a variety of settings and locations. Experience  shooting table top, architecture, nature, portrait, and live action. Adept at lighting and creative eye for composition. Skilled in photo retouching, color correction and manipulation. Manages photo archives, tags and provides digital photo files to Librarian.

raw_data.title: Post Production Supervisor
raw_data.description: Member of internal review team. Supervises post-production team of editors, audio, and graphics. Reviews, comments and signs off on rough/first cuts of all projects prior to client submission.

raw_data.title: Power Point Designer*
raw_data.description: Responsible for creating or re-creating client presentations for web, video and live presentations. Responsible for design, layout, color, fonts; locates, clears and incorporates photos, graphs, charts, diagrams to visually enhance learning and retention.

raw_data.title: Producer (Field)
raw_data.description: Serves as lead on field and studio shoots. Oversees production crew while on shoots. Ensures media acquisition is consistent with script and shot sheet. Responsible for securing release forms; books crew travel, coordinates crew for call times.

raw_data.title: Producer (Senior) Production Lead
raw_data.description: Member of internal review team. Responsible for oversight and direction of individual client task or work orders. Responsible for project oversight. Manages, instructs and organizes production across all departments; responsible for managing production budget; hiring and managing cast and crew.

raw_data.title: Production Assistant
raw_data.description: Assists Director, Producer, DP and other crew members as needed in field and studio production. Responsibilities range from administrative to grip assist.

raw_data.title: Production Coordinator
raw_data.description: Responsible for project coordination and scheduling; staffs production crew for field and studio shoots; maintains equipment inventory. Responsible for equipment ordering and repair.

raw_data.title: Proofreader - Copy Editor
raw_data.description: Member of internal review team.Reviews products for content accuracy against information provided prior to client submission. May suggest text edits to improve readability or clearer organization of information.

raw_data.title: Property Manager
raw_data.description: Works under Art Director/Set Designer.Develops and maintains ongoing list of props needed for scenes/shoots, responsible for creating or procuring props both borrowed and purchased. Responsible for timely return of borrowed props, organizing, labeling and storing, or reselling purchased props or other set items at conclusion of production.

raw_data.title: Researcher*
raw_data.description: Assists scriptwriters by researching, gathering, and cross-referencing background information to support script and creative development efforts. Supports graphics department in securing photos, maps, charts, graphs for use in project. Provides Media Librarian with artist/photographer crediting and licenses for selected media.

raw_data.title: Senior Level Media Consultant
raw_data.description: Responsible for troubleshooting, aiding client with internet, webinar, etc. where audio and video integration is required. Must be current in the latest technologies, hardware and software.
raw_data.education_and_experience_substitution: 10 yrs experience as Senior Level Editor

labor_categories.years_experience: 10 yrs experience as Senior Level Editor

raw_data.title: Technical Director
raw_data.description: Responsible for live or live-to-tape camera switching.

raw_data.title: Teleprompter Operator*
raw_data.description: Prepares and formats client media for traditional teleprompter or power flip software (power point) use. Responsible for set-up and operation of teleprompter hardware and software. One year experience in production. Includes operator, teleprompter, camera mount, laptop, and software.

raw_data.title: Transcriptionist (English)*
raw_data.description: Responsible for transcribing raw footage interviews per time code for both client and scriptwriter to support sound bite selection and development of final script. Responsible for transcribing finished project incorporating SOTs, on camera interviews, sound bites, on camera and voice over narration in support of Section 508 compliance for open and/or closed captioning.

raw_data.title: Videographer (HD)*
raw_data.description: Responsible for High-Definition camera set-up and operation in both field and studio settings; creative understanding of shot composition, moves, pans, tilts, zooms and white balance. Working knowledge of audio inputs and monitoring.
raw_data.education_and_experience_substitution: 10 yrs experience in both field and studio videography

labor_categories.years_experience: 10 yrs experience in both field and studio videography

raw_data.title: Videographer (HD)* Second Cam
raw_data.description: Supports DP or primary Videographer when a second or third camera is needed for pickup shots, cutaways, or additional camera angles. Responsible for helping with camera set-up and operation in both field and studio settings; creative understanding of shot composition, moves, pans, tilts, zooms and white balance. Working knowledge of audio inputs and monitoring.

raw_data.title: Videographer (broll)*
raw_data.description: Responsible for camera set-up and operation in both field and studio settings; must have creative ability to capture beauties, additional pick up shots, and supporting visuals to complete and enhance principle photography.

raw_data.title: Writer (Copywriter)*
raw_data.description: Responsible for writing print copy to include brochures, articles, pamphlets, press releases, reports, manuals, and one-sheets. Writes, proofreads, and edits documents and copy content for publishing or print advertising. Assists in collecting and organizing information required for preparation of articles, reports, brochures, books and/or manuals. Coordinates copywriting with graphic layout and production of the final document.

raw_data.title: Writer (Scriptwriter)*
raw_data.description: Responsible for researching and interviewing both clients and SME's to gather script content. Outlines and drafts non-print script copy for Senior Writer.

raw_data.title: Writer (Senior)*
raw_data.description: Responsible for drafting, revising and submitting film, television, radio or video scripts. Final scripts include both audio and visual content per industry standards.

raw_data.title: Writer (Social Media)*
raw_data.description: Responsible for writing web content; updating and posting to blogs, Facebook, twitter, and other social media outlets. Supports client brand through positive messaging on social media outlets.
